title: Test
summary: This line chart has an x axis representing Year and a y axis representing Unemployment rate, with a total of 11 data points.
Overall Unemployment rate has decreased over the Year.

Unemployment rate is roughly constant from 2014 to 2016, gradually decreasing from 2016 to 2018, roughly constant from 2018 to 2019, slightly increasing from 2019 to 2022, and lastly roughly constant from 2022 to 2024.
The steepest decrease occurs in between the Year 2016 and 2017.
Max Unemployment rate about 6.99 was recorded at Year 2016
Min Unemployment rate about 5.79 was recorded at Year 2019
This line chart has an x axis representing Year and a y axis representing Unemployment rate, with a total of 11 data points. The chart has 3 significant trends.
The longest trend is extremely increasing which exists from 2019 to 2024.
Additionally, the next significant trend is slightly decreasing which exists from 2016 to 2019.
Contrarily, the next significant trend is extremely increasing which exists from 2014 to 2016.
